==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Syn-
<hw>Syn-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Gr. <grk>sy`n</grk> with.]</ety>
<def>A prefix meaning <xex>with</xex>, <xex>along with</xex>,
<xex>together</xex>, <xex>at the same time</xex>. <xex>Syn-</xex>
becomes <xex>sym-</xex> before <xex>p</xex>, <xex>b</xex>, and
<xex>m</xex>, and <xex>syl-</xex> before <xex>l</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Synacmy</ent>⟦br⟧
